Title: Programmer Analyst (Waukegan, IL)
Job_Description:
DevOps Engineer
Remote
Public Trust

Nationwide IT Services (NIS) is seeking a DevOps Engineer to support a development team.
The ideal candidate will be well-versed in DevOps best practices, tools and technologies and work with the development team to deploy and manage code changes and ensure that systems are operational and running smoothly. The DevOps Engineer will report directly to the Task Lead, participate in Agile/Scrum ceremonies/activities as well as provide regular updates on progress/issues/concerns.

Duties and Responsibilities
Git/SCM: Strong Git skills and understanding of Git workflows with substantial experience with source code management platforms (such as GitHub and Gitlab), to implement GitOps and Git-driven pipelines.
• TDD & CI/CD: Support a Test-Driven Development (TDD) team with continuous integration and deployment workflows (CI/CD), including artifact-base development/deployment.
Bonus for experience using Drupal Test Traits (DTT).
• Containers: Architecting and configuring containerized applications; particularly with Docker, and common local Drupal development tools such as Lando, Docksal, DDev Docker for Drupal, and DrupalVM.
• Orchestration (CI/CD): Architecting, configuring and managing both manual and continuous integration, with Kubernetes, GitLab CI, Jenkins, Ansible, and occasionally Chef or Puppet.
• Development Workflow: Architecting, documenting and helping implement local development setup and workflows (QA/UAT, Dev/Test/Prod) for project teams (primarily GitLab, Docker and K8S).
• DB: Configuration and management of common Drupal databases, including MySQL, MariaDB, Aurora/RDS; bonus for PostgreSQL experience (particularly associated with Atlassian, Jira and Confluence configuration/management).
• OS & Web Servers: General systems administration (Linux/Ubuntu) and web server setup / administration (Apache, NGINX, Proxy Servers).
• AWS: Administering multiple AWS-based services, including Lambda, EC2, EBS, ELB, RDS, S3, Route53, EKS, IAM, KMS, CloudWatch, CloudTrail, and Cloud Formation.
• Acquia & Other Hosting Platforms: Extensive work with Acquia (ACE & ACSF), and also with other platform providers, such as Patheon (Multidev & Upstreams), Azure DevOps, Google Cloud Platform (GCP/GKE), CentOS.
• Caching: Configuration of common caching strategies and tools related to Drupal, including Big Pipe, open-source options (Varnish, Memcached, Redis) and major platforms (Akami, Cloudflare).
• Security: Architecting and configuring SecOps, including SSL (LE/certbot and other providers), SSH (OpenSSH, Bastillion), and secrets management (Vault), firewalls.
• Performance: Integration and managing tooling for performance tuning (New Relic) and load testing (Gatling, Artillery, Loader).
• Other: Other general DevOps and systems administration tasks, such as cron, logging / log streaming, search (Solr, Elastic Search), SecOps (not required, but beneficial), and release management.


Must be US Citizen or Authorized to Work in the United States.
• Must be able to attain/maintain Public Trust clearance.
• Excellent verbal/written communication skills
• 5+ years of DevOps experience within an AWS environment
• Bachelor’s in computer science or comparable degree/enterprise work experience desired.


• Familiarity with Acquia/Drupal highly preferred but not required
• AWS and/or Drupal 8 & 9 certifications highly preferred but not required

The Institute for Genomic Medicine (IGM) at Nationwide Children’s Hospital is creating a future that integrates genomics into the everyday practice of pediatrics. Title: Products & Services System Analyst
Job_Description:
Symetra has an exciting opportunity to join our team as an Associate CLO Research Analyst!

About the role
In this newly created role to support the continued growth of Symetra’s Structured Credit portfolio you will work closely with the Director of Structured Products, focus on providing quantitative/analytical and qualitative support for all aspects of Symetra’s CLO portfolio while also gaining exposure to additional structured asset classes. Your primary responsibilities include surveillance and monitoring of the CLO portfolio, manager evaluation and assessment including on-site reviews, evaluation of new issue and secondary opportunities including pool quality and relative value, and assisting with reviews of CLO legal documentation. In addition to supporting the day-to-day management of the CLO portfolio, you’ll be tasked with maintaining and enhancing analytical and reporting tools essential to Symetra's platform. This role will also provide the opportunity to gain exposure to Symetra’s diverse Structured Credit portfolio more generally, with the ability to work with other asset classes as required.

Title: Products & Services System Analyst
Job_Description:
About FAIR Health
FAIR Health, Inc., an independent nonprofit organization, was established in October 2009 with the mission to help assure fairness and transparency in health insurance information. FAIR Health has created a database of over 36 billion de-identified private healthcare claim records—the largest in the country—which receives claims monthly and which serves as the foundation for a variety of data products, custom analytics and consumer tools. FAIR Health has also been certified by CMS as a “Qualified Entity” and thus holds the entire collection of Medicare Parts A, B and D claims from 2013 to the present, which get routinely refreshed.
Our standard data modules, custom analytics and technological tools serve all participants in the healthcare sector nationwide; they are licensed to payors, third-party administrators, bill review companies, self-insured employers, government agencies, academic researchers and consultants. Our medical and dental data are used to inform statutes and regulations, healthcare cost indices, fee schedules, benefit and provider network design, practice/facility expansion, health systems research and dispute resolution, among other uses. We also offer a suite of consumer-oriented tools and resources available on our consumer website (fairhealthconsumer.org), as well as a mobile application, which can be licensed by other organizations.

Title: Products & Services System Analyst
Job_Description:
New Light Technologies Inc. (NLT), an industry-leading full-stack data science engineering consultancy based in Washington DC, is currently seeking full-time Geospatial Analysts to join a team of talented scientists and technology professionals building and managing information solutions that support missions critical to our nation’s communities, environment, economy, and public safety.
Candidates will work in a fast-paced multi-disciplinary environment among a team of talented and dedicated tech professionals across a variety of fields and customers including Emergency Management, Operational Intelligence, Remote Sensing, Geospatial Information Systems, Information Technology, and more. Candidates will work with our growing interdisciplinary team and will perform GIS, imagery and remote sensing analysis, design and document workflows and scripting, help design and maintain geospatial databases and advice on the development of workflows and data pipeline solutions. The candidate will help access, organize, review and publish complex geospatial data and analytics within operational environments for a range of missions, including information assurance, atmospheric and Earth sciences, economics, and more. Working closely with specialists in cloud administration and DevOps, the successful candidate will support the full lifecycle of NLT's operations, including gathering, designing, developing, testing/validating, and implementing complex data analysis processes, and visualizing complex data. i The candidate will also be responsible for maintaining a large repository of nationwide geospatial data sets in vector and raster formats. These data are provided in disparate source formats, so the candidate must have experience working with both databases and APIs and possess excellent data discovery and documentation skills. The candidate will be responsible for data storage and secure data transfer in the cloud (AWS) and should be familiar with overcoming challenges associated with processing big data -including geospatial data. This position requires a leader, innovator, and problem-solver with solid data engineering and management experience and expertise with a range of data, including various imagery formats. This position also requires experience developing and designing new projects and solutions, coordinating projects between multiple teams with many stakeholders, and a pro-active, enthusiastic communication style.

Title: Senior Licensing Specialist
Job_Description:
About FAIR Health
FAIR Health, Inc., a national, independent nonprofit organization, was established in October 2009 with the mission to help assure fairness and transparency in health insurance information. FAIR Health has created a database of over 38 billion de-identified private healthcare claim records—the largest in the country—which receives claims monthly and which serves as the foundation for a variety of data products, custom analytics and consumer tools. FAIR Health has also been certified by the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services as a “Qualified Entity” and thus holds the entire collection of Medicare Parts A, B and D claims from 2013 to the present, which get routinely refreshed.
Our standard data modules, custom analytics and technological tools serve all participants in the healthcare sector nationwide; they are licensed to payors, third-party administrators, bill review companies, self-insured employers, government agencies, academic researchers and consultants. Our medical and dental data are used to inform statutes and regulations, healthcare cost indices, fee schedules, benefit and provider network design, practice/facility expansion, health systems research and dispute resolution, among other uses. We also offer a suite of consumer-oriented tools and resources available on our consumer website (fairhealthconsumer.org), as well as a mobile application, which can be licensed by other organizations.

Title: Senior Licensing Specialist
Job_Description:
New Light Technologies Inc. (NLT), an industry-leading full-stack data science engineering consultancy based in Washington DC, is currently seeking full-time Geospatial Analysts to join a team of talented scientists and technology professionals building and managing information solutions that support missions critical to our nation’s communities, environment, economy, and public safety.
Candidates will work in a fast-paced multi-disciplinary environment among a team of talented and dedicated tech professionals across a variety of fields and customers including Emergency Management, Operational Intelligence, Remote Sensing, Geospatial Information Systems, Information Technology, and more. Candidates will work with our growing interdisciplinary team and will perform GIS, imagery and remote sensing analysis, design and document workflows and scripting, help design and maintain geospatial databases and advice on the development of workflows and data pipeline solutions. The candidate will help access, organize, review and publish complex geospatial data and analytics within operational environments for a range of missions, including information assurance, atmospheric and Earth sciences, economics, and more. Working closely with specialists in cloud administration and DevOps, the successful candidate will support the full lifecycle of NLT's operations, including gathering, designing, developing, testing/validating, and implementing complex data analysis processes, and visualizing complex data. i The candidate will also be responsible for maintaining a large repository of nationwide geospatial data sets in vector and raster formats. These data are provided in disparate source formats, so the candidate must have experience working with both databases and APIs and possess excellent data discovery and documentation skills. The candidate will be responsible for data storage and secure data transfer in the cloud (AWS) and should be familiar with overcoming challenges associated with processing big data -including geospatial data. This position requires a leader, innovator, and problem-solver with solid data engineering and management experience and expertise with a range of data, including various imagery formats. This position also requires experience developing and designing new projects and solutions, coordinating projects between multiple teams with many stakeholders, and a pro-active, enthusiastic communication style.

Title: DevOps Engineer
Job_Description:
DevOps Engineer
Remote
Public Trust

Nationwide IT Services (NIS) is seeking a DevOps Engineer to support a development team.
The ideal candidate will be well-versed in DevOps best practices, tools and technologies and work with the development team to deploy and manage code changes and ensure that systems are operational and running smoothly. The DevOps Engineer will report directly to the Task Lead, participate in Agile/Scrum ceremonies/activities as well as provide regular updates on progress/issues/concerns.

Duties and Responsibilities
Git/SCM: Strong Git skills and understanding of Git workflows with substantial experience with source code management platforms (such as GitHub and Gitlab), to implement GitOps and Git-driven pipelines.
• TDD & CI/CD: Support a Test-Driven Development (TDD) team with continuous integration and deployment workflows (CI/CD), including artifact-base development/deployment.
Bonus for experience using Drupal Test Traits (DTT).
• Containers: Architecting and configuring containerized applications; particularly with Docker, and common local Drupal development tools such as Lando, Docksal, DDev Docker for Drupal, and DrupalVM.
• Orchestration (CI/CD): Architecting, configuring and managing both manual and continuous integration, with Kubernetes, GitLab CI, Jenkins, Ansible, and occasionally Chef or Puppet.
• Development Workflow: Architecting, documenting and helping implement local development setup and workflows (QA/UAT, Dev/Test/Prod) for project teams (primarily GitLab, Docker and K8S).
• DB: Configuration and management of common Drupal databases, including MySQL, MariaDB, Aurora/RDS; bonus for PostgreSQL experience (particularly associated with Atlassian, Jira and Confluence configuration/management).
• OS & Web Servers: General systems administration (Linux/Ubuntu) and web server setup / administration (Apache, NGINX, Proxy Servers).
• AWS: Administering multiple AWS-based services, including Lambda, EC2, EBS, ELB, RDS, S3, Route53, EKS, IAM, KMS, CloudWatch, CloudTrail, and Cloud Formation.
• Acquia & Other Hosting Platforms: Extensive work with Acquia (ACE & ACSF), and also with other platform providers, such as Patheon (Multidev & Upstreams), Azure DevOps, Google Cloud Platform (GCP/GKE), CentOS.
• Caching: Configuration of common caching strategies and tools related to Drupal, including Big Pipe, open-source options (Varnish, Memcached, Redis) and major platforms (Akami, Cloudflare).
• Security: Architecting and configuring SecOps, including SSL (LE/certbot and other providers), SSH (OpenSSH, Bastillion), and secrets management (Vault), firewalls.
• Performance: Integration and managing tooling for performance tuning (New Relic) and load testing (Gatling, Artillery, Loader).
• Other: Other general DevOps and systems administration tasks, such as cron, logging / log streaming, search (Solr, Elastic Search), SecOps (not required, but beneficial), and release management.


Must be US Citizen or Authorized to Work in the United States.
• Must be able to attain/maintain Public Trust clearance.
• Excellent verbal/written communication skills
• 5+ years of DevOps experience within an AWS environment
• Bachelor’s in computer science or comparable degree/enterprise work experience desired.


• Familiarity with Acquia/Drupal highly preferred but not required
• AWS and/or Drupal 8 & 9 certifications highly preferred but not required


NIS is an IT and Management consulting company, designated 8(a) by the SBA, and a CVE-verified Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business. Our mission is to deliver value-added services to our customers, leveraging technology, people, and industry best practices to implement innovative solutions through our trusted employees and team members.

Our benefits package includes medical, dental, and vision insurance, life and disability insurance, 401(k) plan with employer match, paid holidays, PTO (sick/vacation), commuter benefits, employee assistance program (EAP) and educational reimbursement.

Travelers Data Engineering and Data scientists leverage the various compute capabilities in cloud to create transformative predictive models for business. The Data engineer II - MLOPs will support the data engineers and data scientists by creating easy to use pipelines for training and deployment of these models in cloud. The position requires a deep understanding of predictive modeling lifecycle, for both conventional gradient boost type models to deep learning models and a solid understanding of CICD principles. Title: Data and Analytics Architect
Job_Description:
Senior Machine Learning Engineer
Remote within OR or WA
Cambia Health Solutions is working to create a seamless and frictionless health care experience for consumers nationwide. This presents a unique challenge and opportunity for innovative solutions.
Our Machine Learning Engineers in the AI Engineering team design, develop, and implement end-to-end cloud-based machine learning production pipelines (data exploration, sampling, training dataset generation, feature engineering, model building, and performance evaluation) with high availability for a wide variety of health-related projects with opportunity to improve the health quality of millions. You should be passionate about finding insights in data, comfortable with large and fragmented data sets, and command a variety of ML/AI toolsets at your disposal.
In addition to quantitative mastery, the team will effectively interpret and communicate strategic results to varied audiences and provide analytical support for companywide processes and operational improvement efforts. The ideal candidate is an independent, solution-oriented thinker with a strong Computer Science background, full stack software engineering skills, practical experience in machine learning and real-world experience in building end-to-end ML/AI solutions.

Pilot Flying J is the 10th largest privately held company in North America with more than 28,000 team members. Title: Business Analyst
Job_Description:
Business Analyst
Remote
Public Trust

Position Overview:
Nationwide IT Services (NIS) is seeking an experienced Business Analyst to support multiple Federal clients. The Business Analyst will be responsible for supporting new tasks around modernization of legacy applications/systems, which will require analysis of as-is and to-be states as well as documentation of existing processes, documentation for requirements to develop software application features, requirements for application and website migration, market research of viable technical solutions and recommendations to the customer.

The Business Analyst will also be responsible for supporting development teams as needed for the elicitation and documentation of project requirements. The Business Analyst will report to the Program Manager and Project Manager and provide weekly updates on project status/issues/risks.


• 3-5 years of Business Analyst experience in the IT field
• Great analytical, critical thinking and problem-solving abilities
• Excellent verbal/written communication skills
• Superior management and organizational skills
• Ability to multi-task and support multiple tasks/activities
• Experience with Backlog Grooming sessions with the client and development team
• Familiarity/experience with software development methodologies and best practices such as Waterfall and Agile/Scrum
• Familiarity/experience with software issue tracking tools such as Jira
• Must be US Citizen or Authorized to Work in the United States
• Ability to obtain and retain a Public Trust clearance


• Bachelor’s Degree in technical field is preferred


NIS is an IT and Management consulting company, designated 8(a) by the SBA, and a CVE-verified Service Disabled Veteran Owned Small Business. Our mission is to deliver value-added services to our customers, leveraging technology, people, and industry best practices to implement innovative solutions through our trusted employees and team members.

Our benefits package includes medical, dental, and vision insurance, life and disability insurance, 401(k) plan with employer match, paid holidays, PTO (sick/vacation), commuter benefits, employee assistance program (EAP) and educational reimbursement.

Nationwide IT Services, Inc. provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all qualified applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, genetics, disability or protected veteran status.

Title: Business Analyst
Job_Description:
Overview:
RDC Data Analyst - Research

The Research Institute at Nationwide Children’s Hospital is looking for a Data Analyst to join the RISI Research & Development division. The Data analyst will provide data support, especially in the area of clinical data query & extraction from Clarity, EDW, or Research Data Warehouse. The Data Analyst will be involved in requirement intake/analysis, mapping, extracting, and integrating internal and external data sources, troubleshooting data quality related issues, and documenting existing data elements by maintaining the data dictionary. This role will develop and rely on the knowledge of clinical work and data flow, understand data model, data relationship and dependency, and be able to translate ad-hoc customer request into SQL statements to retrieve data, analyze results, then provide timely and appropriate reports or data extract. The Data analyst will also provide support with Electronic Data Capture (EDC) systems or applications such as REDCap and OpenClinica. The Data Analyst will be involved with designing data collection instruments and study configurations. We are looking for a motivated individual with strong problem solving skills. This individual must also be adept at organizing and managing multiple projects simultaneously and working with an interdisciplinary team of stakeholders. Come help to change the world in a job that really matters.

Have a broad range of responsibilities related to the financial and data analytics pertaining to Children’s Community Practices and the Regional Hospitalist Program.

Title: Business Analyst
Job_Description:
As part of the Research and Evaluation team at The Center for Family Safety and Healing, the Evaluation Analyst will help internal and external partners put measures in place to make the impact of our programs visible, and to empower teams to drive their work forward based on data.

Title: Business Analyst
Job_Description:
Overview:
Business Analyst - Data Warehouse

The Business Analyst is responsible for gathering and understanding clinical and business customer requirements that define the overall architecture of systems. This position will directly support the IS Applications Architect design team which provides the discipline to ensure that investments in process, information and technology support the hospital’s strategic goals. This position must have a broad view of enterprise systems and infrastructures, and should have a strong understanding of the healthcare business and an understanding of healthcare technologies. The Business Analyst assists in the development of a long term strategic vision that is used as a context for short-term tactical decisions. The Business Analyst supports the Applications team to create solutions that have affordable and sustainable IT architectures that solve business problems. A Business Analyst should look for interoperable solutions that optimize resources and produce required outcomes. The Business Analyst assists in researching and promoting new technology and industry best practices. The Business Analyst also facilitates change to maximize value and minimize effort.
